    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="750"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <head>No. 747.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Robeson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 8, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">Confidential.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose ten copies of an
                    arrangement made this day between me and the Spanish minister for the surrender
                    of the Virginius, and the survivors of those who were on board of her when
                    captured, and for the salute to the flag, should one be made, and ten copies of
                    the message of the President, with the protocol of the 29th November, on the
                    same subject. Referring to our conversation this afternoon, may I request that
                    the proper instructions may be given <pb facs="1204" n="1108" xml:id="pg_1108"/>
                    without delay and in the manner indicated by you verbally, or in such other way
                    as may seem to you best, in order that the said arrangement may be promptly
                    carried out?</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P. S.—The copies referred to were delivered to Mr. Robeson personally this
                        p.m.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
